			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">On x86_64, initial stack prepared for the nacl process contains 64-bit argument count, while all other entries are 32-bit (as expected for ILP32).

We didn't try to fix this, as there are several assembly code pieces in glibc and other places that handle argc with push/pop, which is 64-bit only on x86_64.

Probably this has to be fixed at some point.
